DB-CouchDB-Magic

This is an extension of DB::CouchDB that handles some corner cases with
extension functions. This will most likely be obsolete some time but for
now it is a live safer. Look into the man page for the additional
functions and into the DB::CouchDB man page for general usage.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc DB::CouchDB::Magic

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=DB-CouchDB-Magic

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/DB-CouchDB-Magic

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/DB-CouchDB-Magic

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/DB-CouchDB-Magic/


